                            <comment id="13807466" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 28 Oct 2013 23:27:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Did you figure out why the test fails in 0.94 (see last comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9593&quot; title=&quot;Region server left in online servers list forever if it went down after registering to master and before creating ephemeral node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9593&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9593&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br/&gt;
I would like to pull this into 0.94.13.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807490" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 28 Oct 2013 23:52:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test fails a bit cryptically with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
testRSTermnationAfterRegisteringToMasterBeforeCreatingEphemeralNod(org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.TestRSKilledWhenInitializing)  Time elapsed: 180.009 sec  &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; ERROR!
java.lang.Exception: test timed out after 180000 milliseconds
        at java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.arraycopy(Native Method)
        at java.lang.AbstractStringBuilder.deleteCharAt(AbstractStringBuilder.java:771)
        at java.lang.StringBuilder.deleteCharAt(StringBuilder.java:263)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.jmx.MBeanRegistry.makeObjectName(MBeanRegistry.java:206)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.jmx.MBeanRegistry.unregister(MBeanRegistry.java:115)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.jmx.MBeanRegistry.unregister(MBeanRegistry.java:132)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.server.ServerCnxnFactory.unregisterConnection(ServerCnxnFactory.java:137)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.server.NIOServerCnxn.close(NIOServerCnxn.java:972)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.server.NIOServerCnxnFactory.closeAll(NIOServerCnxnFactory.java:243)
        at org.apache.zookeeper.server.NIOServerCnxnFactory.shutdown(NIOServerCnxnFactory.java:254)
        at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.zookeeper.MiniZooKeeperCluster.shutdown(MiniZooKeeperCluster.java:222)
        at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.HBaseTestingUtility.shutdownMiniZKCluster(HBaseTestingUtility.java:533)
        at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.TestRSKilledWhenInitializing.testRSTermnationAfterRegisteringToMasterBeforeCreatingEphemeralNod(TestRSKilledWhenInitializing.java:101)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807513" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 00:16:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Figured out why the test fails. It&apos;s race on the firstRS boolean. If I replace that with an AtomicBoolean it passes fine.&lt;br/&gt;
Looks like is also wrong on the trunk patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807516" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 00:19:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch with fixed test.&lt;br/&gt;
Unless I hear objections I&apos;ll commit this tonight or tomorrow morning.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807665" author="rajesh23" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 04:30:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Lars for fixing the test case.&lt;br/&gt;
The 0.94 patch at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9593&quot; title=&quot;Region server left in online servers list forever if it went down after registering to master and before creating ephemeral node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9593&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9593&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is hanging because we have only one regionserver which is getting killed. But during master initialization we will retry infinitely until root region assigned. Since there are no regionsevers keep retry to assign ROOT. In the current patch I have added one more region server to open the &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; and .META. regions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Looks like is also wrong on the trunk patch.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In trunk patch starting 1 RS only. After the RS killed there wont be any regionserver still master initialization not waiting for meta region to assign. I think the reason for that is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9151&quot; title=&quot;HBCK cannot fix when meta server znode deleted, this can happen if all region servers stopped and there are no logs to split.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9151&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9151&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(When meta server znode deleted and meta in FAILED_OPEN state, then hbck cannot fix it. This scenario can come when all region servers stopped by stop command and didnt start any RS within 10 secs(with default configurations).)&lt;br/&gt;
I will check that as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9151&quot; title=&quot;HBCK cannot fix when meta server znode deleted, this can happen if all region servers stopped and there are no logs to split.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9151&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9151&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807687" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 05:18:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rajesh23&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rajesh23&quot;&gt;rajeshbabu&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
You&apos;re good with the patch you posted here? (I mean including the test fix)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807698" author="rajesh23" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 05:41:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its fine Lars. I have tested the same in the cluster also. Its working fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13807701" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2013 05:45:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.94. Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rajesh23&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rajesh23&quot;&gt;rajeshbabu&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
